Oh, I should point out that that is for the new syntax, so that's probably wrong.  You get better compatibility (for the moment) using:

```js
    const localCurve = crypto.createECDH('prime256v1');
    localCurve.generateKeys();
    //....
    const cipherText = ece.encrypt(bufferPayload, {
      version: 'aesgcm',
      privateKey: localCurve,
      dh: subscription.keys.p256dh,
      authSecret: subscription.keys.auth
    })
```

Give it a few months and we'll have rolled out the new version in browsers, but this is the best choice for the moment.  Ultimately, the ideal method will depend on you passing version from the first element of [PushManager.supportedContentEncodings](https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#dom-pushmanager), but that's even further out.

