@seanzxx You're Welcome. Thanks for incorporating -E / -X  I think that the only think left would be checking the OS version. In my [suggested PR](https://github.com/thshdw/sshuttle/commit/b4d41c3125b938c4051afc24f3ba85b28eec1362) I do this:
```
	if sys.platform == "darwin":
            pfctl('-a', 'com.apple/sshuttle', '-f', '/etc/pf-sshuttle.conf', '-E')
	else:
	    pfctl('-Ef', pf_config_file)
        os.remove(pf_config_file)
    else:
	token_cmd = shlex.split('sudo pfctl -a com.apple/sshuttle -s Reference')
        token_process = ssubprocess.Popen(token_cmd, stdout=ssubprocess.PIPE).communicate()[0]
        match_token = re.search(r"\s\W\D[0-9]*\b\D\W", token_process)  
        if match_token is not None:
            pfctl_token = match_token.group()	
	    pfctl('-X', pfctl_token.strip())
	else:
	    pfctl('-dF', 'all')
```
I do this because ```-E``` and ```-X``` are OS X specific switches. With non OS X installs that use pfctl we need to use ```-e``` see the OpenBSD [man page for pfctl](http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi/OpenBSD-current/man8/pfctl.8?query=pfctl) 

