It might be due to some issue with mixing threading and tornado IOLoop. The scheduler is used within the keep-alive thread meaning that two `run_sync` call could be done at the same time to the same IOLoop. Based on my understanding of tornado event loop, that's bad. Creating the `SimpleAsyncHTTPClient` just before the request would solve the issue (if I'm right). The http client would be associated with the thread IOLoop and the described issue couldn't occur. However I'm in favor of a revert here. It seemed neat for the testing to use the Tornado httpclient however, I would rather go with the save option and use the urllib client (If it wasn't from dependency issues I would requests thou).

